X. How Long Do We Keep Your Personal Information?
We keep your personal information to enable your continued use of our Services, for as long as it is required in order to fulfill the relevant purposes described in this Privacy Policy, as may be required by law such as for tax and accounting purposes, or as otherwise communicated to you. For example, we retain your transaction history so that you can review past purchases (and repeat orders if desired) and what addresses you have shipped orders to, and to safeguard your privacy right.
XI. Users From The European Union?
For European-resident Users, you may refer to this part for special regulation under GDPR (General Data Protection Regulation).
You may reserve the right pursuant to GDPR:
* Right of access by the data subject.
You no matter as a visitor or a customer, are as a user, entitled to access their own information to confirm whether their personal data are being process or not. Users have the right to know about the detailed information:
o the purposes of the processing;
o the categories of personal data;
o the recipients or categories of recipient to whom the personal data have been disclosed to;
o the time frame for the personal data concerned stored;
o the existence of automated decision-making.
* Right to rectification.
Users have the right to rectify the data. If your information is incorrect or incomplete. You may choose to correct and complete the information or inform us to assist you doing so.
* Right to erasure.
You are users conferred the right to request us to delete your personal information. We will use the available technology to erase your personal information, including but not limited to pseudonymization, de identification, clearing and other erasure methods. However, for the reason of exercising the right of freedom of expression and information, compliance of legal obligations, public interest in public health,archiving purposes in the public interest, scientific or historical research purposes or statistical purposes, or for legitimate defence.
* Right to restriction of processing.
Users shall be aware of that before you request for certain right, you are supposed to cooperate with us for verify your personal information and your identity. In verification process, you shall include your name, address, and/or email address when you contact us. We will take reasonable steps to verify your identity prior to responding to your requests. The verification steps will vary depending on the sensitivity of your personal information and whether you have an account with us, but we will make a response to you within the specified time set under GDPR.
* Right to data portability.
You may request for your personal data provided to us on basis of consent or contract, or the automated processing to a third party under the condition of availability of the technology. Whether feasible or not, please contact our Customer Service for confirmation. You shall be assured that we will attempt to guarantee your data to be transmitted to a third party in a structed, commonly used and machined-readable format where technically feasible.
* Right to object.
You may object to the direct marketing and you can view
