XII. Users From California?
For U.S. California-resident Users, you may refer to this part for special regulation under CCPA (California Consumer Protection Act).
You may keep the right pursuant to CCPA:
* Right to know.
California residents have the right to request disclosure of the following information:
o  the categories of personal information that we have collected about you;
o the categories of sources from which we have collected personal information about you;
o the business or commercial purpose for collecting or selling your personal information;
o the categories of personal information that we have sold about you and the categories of outside parties to whom the personal information was sold;
o the categories of personal information that we have disclosed about you for our business purposes and the categories of vendors to whom the personal information was disclosed; and the specific pieces of personal information that we have collected about you.
* Right to require deletion of consumer personal Information.
Identical to the regulation of GDPR, you remain the right to delete your personal information from us. We will observe your instructions to delete the demanded information unless we inform the reasons, except for:
o completing the transaction;
o detecting security incidents; protect against malicious, deceptive, fraudulent, or illegal activity, or prosecute those responsible for that activity;
o repairing, restoring or amending the goods you purchased;
o exercising individual’s free speech;
o Performing the obligation under the California Electronic Communications Privacy Act;
o Engaging scientific, historical, or statistical public-interest research in limited circumstances;
o Solely internal uses that are reasonably aligned with your interest when you use our service;
o Legal obligation required;
* Right to opt out of the sale of personal information
. WE DO NOT SELL YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION.  You do not need to worry about the right to opt out of the sale of personal information.
* Right to equal service and non-discrimination.
We promise we will not conduct unfair trade because of any exercise of rights under CCPA.
* Right to establish mechanism to data access.
When you exercise any of the rights abovementioned, you shall be verified in the first place. If you have any questions, please contact our Customer Service and Data Protection Officer. We will respond to you electronically within the period stipulated pursuant to CCPA.
* Shine the Light.
California's Shine the Light Act entitles California users to request information concerning whether a business has disclosed certain information about you to any third parties for the third parties’ direct marketing purposes. California users who wish to request further information in compliance with this law or have questions or concerns about our privacy practices and policies may contact us at
dataprotectionofficer@ador.com
. We accept your agent with a power of attorney evidencing you are fully authorized to exercise any rights available to you on your behalf.
